---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Palindrome Words in Scrabble — Words That Read Both Ways"
  description="Discover palindrome words valid in Scrabble — words that read the same forwards and backwards. KAYAK, LEVEL, CIVIC, ROTOR and more with point values and strategy."
  keywords="palindrome words scrabble, kayak scrabble, level scrabble, palindrome word list, civic scrabble, words same backwards"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Palindrome Words in Scrabble — Words That Read Both Ways",
    "description": "Discover palindrome words valid in Scrabble — words that read the same forwards and backwards. KAYAK, LEVEL, CIVIC, ROTOR and more.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/palindrome-words-scrabble" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the highest-scoring palindrome in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "KAYAK scores 15 points (K=5, A=1, Y=4, A=1, K=5) making it the highest-scoring common palindrome. LEVEL scores 8 points, CIVIC scores 12 points, and ROTOR scores 5 points. Premium square placement can multiply these significantly." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many palindrome words are valid in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "There are approximately 50-60 palindrome words valid across TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries, ranging from 2-letter words like AA and MM to 7-letter words like DEIFIED and REVIVER. Most playable palindromes are 3-5 letters long." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is RACECAR a valid Scrabble word?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No, RACECAR is not a valid Scrabble word in either TWL or SOWPODS — it's written as two words (race car) or hyphenated. However, palindromes like KAYAK, LEVEL, CIVIC, RADAR, ROTOR, and DEIFIED are all valid plays." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Palindromes</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Palindrome Words in Scrabble</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Palindromes — words that read identically forwards and backwards — are among the most satisfying plays in Scrabble. Beyond their novelty, palindromes have a practical edge: they contain repeated letters, which means if you have doubles on your rack, palindromes might be your best path to a play. From the humble AA to the impressive DEIFIED, here's every palindrome worth knowing for your next game.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Palindrome Stats</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">50+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid Palindromes</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2-7</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter Range</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Max Points (KAYAK)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">DEIFIED</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Longest Common</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>Palindromes appear across every word length. Two-letter palindromes (AA, MM) are obvious, but the 5-7 letter palindromes are where real scoring happens. These words use repeated letters efficiently and often surprise opponents who don't expect them.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Complete Palindrome Word Table</h2>
      <p>All words below read the same forwards and backwards and are valid in at least one official Scrabble dictionary.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Length</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Definition</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">KAYAK</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Small boat</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">REVIVER</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">One who revives</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">CIVIC</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Relating to a city</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">DEIFIED</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Made into a god</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SHAHS</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Persian rulers</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">REPAPER</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To paper again</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MADAM</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Polite form of address</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">LEVEL</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Flat, even surface</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">REFER</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To direct attention</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">ROTATOR</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Something that rotates</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MUM</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Mother / silent</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">POP</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Father / burst</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">RADAR</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Detection system</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SAGAS</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Long stories</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">TENET</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A principle or belief</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">16</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">STATS</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Statistics</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">ROTOR</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Rotating mechanism</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SOLOS</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Lone performances</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">KAYAK</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">15 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">CIVIC</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">REVIVER</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">DEIFIED</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">SHAHS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11 pts</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Fun Facts About Scrabble Palindromes</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔄 Mirror Symmetry</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Palindromes always have odd-length forms (3, 5, 7 letters) with a center letter, or even-length (4, 6) with a mirrored pair. Odd palindromes are far more common in English.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📊 Double Letters Required</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Every palindrome uses at least one letter twice. KAYAK needs 2×K and 2×A. This means duplicate tiles on your rack aren't always bad — they might spell a palindrome.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 Bingo Palindromes</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DEIFIED, REVIVER, and REPAPER are all 7-letter palindromes. Playing them as bingos adds the 50-point bonus — REVIVER as a bingo scores 63 points before premium squares.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎯 K is the Palindrome King</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">KAYAK scores 15 points because K is worth 5 each — and you need two of them. With only 1 K tile in the bag, you'd need a blank for the second K unless hooking onto an existing K.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Duplicate tiles aren't always bad:</span> If you draw two R's, think ROTOR. Two E's? Think LEVEL or REFER. Two S's? Think STATS or SAGAS. Palindromes turn duplicate-heavy racks into playable hands.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">7-letter palindromes are bingo candidates:</span> DEIFIED (12 + 50 = 62 pts), REVIVER (13 + 50 = 63 pts), and REPAPER (11 + 50 = 61 pts) are all achievable bingos. Keep them in mind when you have the right letter combinations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Use blanks for expensive duplicates:</span> KAYAK needs two K tiles but only one K exists. Use a blank as the second K — you still score 10 points for the word (blank=0, K=5, A=1, Y=4, A=1, blank=0).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CIVIC with C on DLS:</span> CIVIC scores 12 base points. If either C lands on a double-letter square, that's 15 points. Both C's on premium squares is rare but devastating — plan your board placement.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">MADAM and LEVEL are everyday words:</span> Don't overlook common palindromes. MADAM (10 pts) and LEVEL (8 pts) use common tiles and fit easily on most boards. They're reliable mid-game plays.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/highest-scoring-scrabble-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Highest Scoring Scrabble Words Ever — Ultimate List</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/best-z-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Z Words in Scrabble — Top Scoring Z Plays</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/letter-frequency-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Letter Frequency in Scrabble — Distribution Guide</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
